    "full_text": "- Hi, I'm Fernando,\n(gentle uplifting music) a district success\nmanager with Khan Academy. Welcome to Khan Academy Reimagined. Now, before we get into what's improving, let me just say I get it. I spent the last 14 years as a teacher and as an administrator. I love Khan Academy for its trusted standards-aligned content, and I know you do too, but let's face it, students didn't always\nfind it engaging and fun. For teachers, it felt\ncrowded and hard to navigate. We're keeping the core of what\nyou love, the great content, along with the support of the latest AI, and we've redesigned everything else based off of years of your feedback. We heard you. The clutter and noise is gone. Your new teacher dashboard\nis simple, intuitive, and designed to give you back time. You'll see the Khanmigo search window, your one-stop shop for\npowerful lesson planning, content discovery, and more. Right below that, your\ninsights for the day. This takes all of the guesswork out of where your students need support. Forget endless data analysis. You'll still get the same reporting, but our AI processes the data for you, telling you exactly\nwhich students need help and providing the precise exercises to get them back on track. With one push of a button, you can even directly assign\nan AI-powered tutoring session. It's like having a data analyst\nand a tutor in your corner. You still keep a close eye on\nwhat your students are saying back and forth with Khanmigo, and are immediately notified\nin this moderation window. Over here, you keep the long-term goals your district sets for you always visible along with reports on progress. We know positive reinforcement works. In a second, I'll tell you about these sparkly little gems over here. Teaching support is simplified, but the real guidance is for the student. Let's check out what the student now sees. (gentle bright music) Students log into a simplified,\ndistraction-free experience. Instead of clutter, they see a clear streamlined\nlearning path you control, showing them exactly what\nthey need to master next. They're always on track and they know it. And when they hit a tough\nspot in an exercise, Khanmigo is there on the side, ready to refresh a concept or\nguide them through a problem, offering support without\never giving away the answer. Research shows that consistent practice drives student progress. Instant feedback helps\nstudents keep trying, correcting, and ultimately\nmastering the skill. (graphic beeping) Remember these gems? Students are saying they love these. As the students rack them\nup with their progress, teachers can use them to go towards things like class pizza parties, extra recess, or whatever goals you want to set. With Khan Academy Reimagined, the teacher in the room\nremains the expert. These tools are designed\nto make life easier, giving more time for small\ngroup or one-on-one instruction. The teacher remains in control. The path between the teacher, the student, and your district's goals\nis now crystal clear. Like I said earlier, a lot of what makes Khan\nAcademy amazing isn't changing, like our commitment to\nyou and your teachers. Our support and success team will be here to help you bring this to\nlife in your classrooms. Ready to see how Khan Academy Reimagined fundamentally shifts teaching\nand learning at your school? Follow the links on the screen and let's set up a time to\nshow you the full experience."
